Lafarge, Anglo American to Sell Assets to Facilitate Merger, FT Reports

-- B y   J o h n   S i m p s o n
-- 
2011-05-08T22:33:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-08/lafarge-anglo-american-to-sell-assets-to-facilitate-merger-ft-reports.html
Lafarge SA (LG)  and  Anglo American Plc (AAL)  are
planning to sell 600 million pounds ($983 million) of cement
plants, quarries and ready-mix concrete plants in the U.K. to
avert anticompetitive action by regulators and pay down debt as
the companies aim to combine their U.K. cement businesses, the
Financial Times reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Simpson at 
 jsimpson12@bloomberg.net  